# Project Description: Full-Stack Banking System

The **Banking System** is a comprehensive, production-ready web application engineered to replicate real-world enterprise banking workflows. It focuses heavily on data integrity, role-based access control, and complete transactional transparency. 

The application architecture cleanly separates concerns into a high-performance, type-safe frontend and a robust, secure relational database backend.

---

## Core Modules & Capabilities

### Customer Portal
*   **Balance Overview:** Real-time visibility of account balances and financial health.
*   **Fund Transfers:** Secure and immediate processing of internal financial transactions.
*   **Account Tracking:** A self-service portal to view account tiers, statuses, and details.
*   **Support & Complaints:** An integrated ticketing system allowing customers to lodge issues directly to administration.

### Admin Command Center
*   **User Management:** Centralized control over customer profiles, account creations, and system access.
*   **Transaction Oversight:** Global ledger view to monitor and review all system-wide financial transactions.
*   **Issue Resolution:** A dedicated workflow to process, update, and resolve customer complaints.
*   **Live Audit Logs:** A high-level view of system actions to track database changes and user operations.

### Security & Integrity
*   **Immutable Audit Logging:** System-wide tracking of critical data mutations to ensure compliance and a tamper-evident history.
*   **Role-Based Access Control (RBAC):** Strict authentication pipelines ensuring users only see the features and data assigned to their verified role.

---

## Architectural & Technical Highlights

*   **Frontend Excellence:** Built using **React** and **TypeScript** via **Vite**, the client-side application guarantees a rapid, type-safe user experience. It leverages **TailwindCSS** for responsive design and **Lucide React** for modern iconography.
*   **Robust Backend API:** A **Node.js** and **Express** server acts as the central orchestrator—exposing secure API endpoints, processing business logic, and handling data validation.
*   **Enterprise Database Management:** Powered by an **Oracle Database**, the system utilizes strict relational schemas, constraints, and permission automation scripts to guarantee data persistence and zero data corruption. It also integrates procedural backend scripts for deeper transaction handling.
